-- Cameroon Arabica Price Rises as Robusta Drops in Week to May 6
-- B y   P i u s   L u k o n g
-- 2012-05-07T10:30:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-07/cameroon-arabica-price-rises-as-robusta-drops-in-week-to-may-6.html
The average export price for arabica
coffee from Cameroon rose 3.7 percent to 1,882  CFA francs 
($3.73) a kilogram (2.2 pounds) in the week to May 6, according
to Bloomberg calculations made using daily export prices from
the Cocoa and Coffee Board.  The price for robusta coffee dropped 1.1 percent to 895
francs a kilogram from a week earlier, the figures, sent in a
mobile-phone text message from the Douala-based board,
indicated.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Pius Lukong in Yaounde via Accra at 
 ebowers1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
